issue.title: Future Improvements/Capabilities
issue.body:
- [ ] Add capability for NLU to send emails **[Network Access]**

- [ ] Allow **user specification**  
Ex.  Current working -> `rename file to file*`
 Potential future working (Inclusive of previous working) ->` rename file in folder to file*`
 Applicable to _copy, move_ as well  eg. `copy file from 'src_folder' to 'dest_folder'`

- [ ] Keep track of commands per session and provide an **undo** mechanism. [Stack]

- [ ] Use open modifier -a to **open application**.

- [ ] The subprocess.Popen() routine could be used directly to **call Unix binaries** such as mv, open, etc. which can eliminate the need for some of the scripts.

- [ ] Create a mapping from a set of extensions to descriptive Folder names.  
Example: _.jpeg, .png, .gif_ etc all go into Images folder  **[Better naming of folders after executing organize]**

- [ ] Programmer mode: Different theme in the UI + Allow users to execute unix commands directly

issue.title: Add command flexibility
issue.body:
Optimize performance by only invoking find when the user hasn't specified enough.

Ex. 
Current working -> rename file to file*

Potential future working (Inclusive of previous working) -> rename file in folder to file*


Applicable to copy, move as well
eg. copy file from 'src_folder' to 'dest_folder'

issue.title: Case sensitivity can impact scripting interface
issue.body: Unix commands expect case-sensitivity, but macOS HFS+, for example, defaults to a case-insensitive filesystem. macOS High Sierra or later uses APFS (case-sensitive). For now, using flag *-iname* instead of *-name* in **find.sh** may resolve this discrepancy, but this must be tested thoroughly.
